<keyLead box="[113,1088,1338,1362]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">1 Wing with membrane unicolorous; posterior cross-vein (dm-cu) absent. .................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,1089,1338,1618]" box="[113,1088,1370,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<keyLead box="[113,1088,1370,1394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
– Wing with fumose cloudings; posterior cross-vein (dm-cu) developed (
<figureCitation box="[930,996,1370,1394]" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="6.[151,188,1521,1540]" captionTargetBox="[187,1094,222,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[187,1095,222,1470]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 1–2. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov. 1 – male holotype, body length ca 3.4 mm; 2 – wing, length 3.1 mm, male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). Photo by J. Roháček." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378011/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). ....... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="249" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,1089,1338,1618]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
<keyLead pageId="19" pageNumber="248">
2(1) Larger species (body length more than 
<quantity box="[598,665,1402,1426]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
). Antennal pedicel (not scape) blackish brown. Ventral part of face yellow, whitish microtomentose and with 5–6 pairs of setae. Mesonotum grey microtomentose with a pair of longitudinal brownish microtomentose vittae. A pair of strong prescutellar ac setae (situated in front of posterior dc) present. Male genitalia with robust elongately triangular surstylus, short subtriangular gonostylus (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." box="[305,547,1562,1586]" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[559,621,1562,1586]" captionStart="Figs 1–2" captionStartId="6.[151,188,1521,1540]" captionTargetBox="[187,1094,222,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[187,1095,222,1470]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 1–2. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov. 1 – male holotype, body length ca 3.4 mm; 2 – wing, length 3.1 mm, male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). Photo by J. Roháček." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378011/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and cercus large, broad and with long setae. ......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1858" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1858" box="[821,1088,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Periscelididae" genus="Periscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulipes">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[821,956,1593,1617]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="248">P. annulipes</emphasis>
Loew, 1858
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1127,219,1140]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
<keyLead pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
– Smaller species (body length distinctly less than 
<quantity box="[730,796,220,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
). Pedicel pale brown, ochreous yellow basally. Ventral part of face brown, grey microtomentose and with only 1 pair of setae. Mesonotum dark grey, with pale grey microtomentum. No prescutellar ac. Male genitalia with very slender and long surstylus, elongately subtriangular gonostylus, and cercus more slender but with robust setae (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." box="[765,1005,348,372]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1016,1114,347,372]" captionStart="Figs 6–10" captionStartId="12.[151,188,1450,1469]" captionTargetBox="[152,1122,222,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-10@12.[149,1130,216,1397]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 6–10. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). 6 – entire genitalia, laterally; 7 – surstylus, laterally; 8 – postgonite, laterally; 9 – gonostylus, sublaterally (widest extension); 10 – cercus, laterally.Scale = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378015/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
). ..................................................................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1127,219,1140]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
<keyLead pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
3(2) Gonostylus longer, hence surstylus less than 1.4 times as long as gonostylus (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." pageId="20" pageNumber="249" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[374,438,443,467]" captionStart="Figs 3–5" captionStartId="7.[113,150,1510,1529]" captionTargetBox="[138,1063,219,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-13@7.[138,1065,219,1454]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 3–5. Periscelis species. 3 – Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype, body dorsally, length ca 3.0 mm (Czech Republic: S. Moravia); 4 – same specimen, laterally; 5 – Periscelis (P.) winnertzii Egger, 1862, male, head and thorax subdorsally, body length ca 4.1 mm (Hungary). Photo by J. Roháček." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378013/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); ejacapodeme more robust and proximally not widened (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." pageId="20" pageNumber="249" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[375,443,475,500]" captionStart="Figs 3–5" captionStartId="7.[113,150,1510,1529]" captionTargetBox="[138,1063,219,1453]" captionTargetId="figure-13@7.[138,1065,219,1454]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 3–5. Periscelis species. 3 – Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype, body dorsally, length ca 3.0 mm (Czech Republic: S. Moravia); 4 – same specimen, laterally; 5 – Periscelis (P.) winnertzii Egger, 1862, male, head and thorax subdorsally, body length ca 4.1 mm (Hungary). Photo by J. Roháček." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378013/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[455,471,475,499]" captionStart="Figs 6–10" captionStartId="12.[151,188,1450,1469]" captionTargetBox="[152,1122,222,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-10@12.[149,1130,216,1397]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 6–10. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). 6 – entire genitalia, laterally; 7 – surstylus, laterally; 8 – postgonite, laterally; 9 – gonostylus, sublaterally (widest extension); 10 – cercus, laterally.Scale = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378015/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">6</figureCitation>
). ........................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="nigra (Zetterstedt, 1860)" authorityName="nigra (Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[769,1126,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Periscelididae" genus="Periscelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nigra" subSpecies="nigra">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[769,921,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">P. nigra nigra</emphasis>
