</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1127,219,1140]" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
<keyLead pageId="20" pageNumber="249">
– Gonostylus shorter, hence surstylus about 1.6 times as long as gonostylus (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." pageId="20" pageNumber="249" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[373,439,539,563]" captionStart="Figs 6–10" captionStartId="12.[151,188,1450,1469]" captionTargetBox="[152,1122,222,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-10@12.[149,1130,216,1397]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 6–10. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). 6 – entire genitalia, laterally; 7 – surstylus, laterally; 8 – postgonite, laterally; 9 – gonostylus, sublaterally (widest extension); 10 – cercus, laterally.Scale = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378015/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[450,479,540,564]" captionStart="Figs 11–14" captionStartId="13.[113,150,1512,1531]" captionTargetBox="[118,1081,425,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-13@13.[111,1092,415,1503]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 11–14. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). 11 – external genitalia caudally (surstyli omitted); 12 – same, cranially (cerci omitted); 13 – pregenital sternum (S6), ventrally; 14 – aedeagal complex, laterally (only basal part of distiphallus depicted). Scale = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[488,517,539,563]" captionStart="Figs 15–21" captionStartId="14.[151,188,1488,1507]" captionTargetBox="[158,1125,385,1457]" captionTargetId="figure-10@14.[149,1130,375,1478]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 15–21.Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., female paratype (Portugal:Valongo). 15 – postabdomen, dorsally; 16 – T8, dorsally; 17 – S8, ventrally; 18 – spermathecae; 19 – ventral receptacle, laterally; 20 – 5th segment and postabdomen, ventrally; 21 – posterior part of postabdomen (from 7th segment), laterally. Scales = 0.2 mm (Figs 15, 20, 21) and 0.1 mm (Figs 16–19). For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378019/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">15</figureCitation>
); ejacapodeme more slender and proximally dilated (
<bibRefCitation author="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P." pageId="20" pageNumber="249" pagination="345 - 371" refId="ref11950" refString="PAPP L. &amp; WITHERS P. 2011: A revision of the Palaearctic Periscelidinae with notes on some New World species (Diptera: Periscelididae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 103: 345 - 371." type="journal article" year="2011">PAPP &amp; WITHERS 2011</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[402,497,571,596]" captionStart="Figs 6–10" captionStartId="12.[151,188,1450,1469]" captionTargetBox="[152,1122,222,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-10@12.[149,1130,216,1397]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 6–10. Periscelis (P.) fugax sp. nov., male paratype (Portugal: Valongo). 6 – entire genitalia, laterally; 7 – surstylus, laterally; 8 – postgonite, laterally; 9 – gonostylus, sublaterally (widest extension); 10 – cercus, laterally.Scale = 0.1 mm. For abbreviations see p. 231." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5378015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5378015/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="249">Figs 7, 9</figureCitation>
